  "title": "QUANTITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities:</p><p>- Prepare cost estimates, BOQs, MTOs, and tender proposals for steel/metal works.</p><p>- Review contracts, drawings, and specs; manage subcontracts and variations.</p><p>- Handle monthly claims, VOs, and final accounts; ensure timely payment and documentation.</p><p>- Track budgets, cost control, and cash flow; prepare reports for management.</p><p>- Liaise with project, engineering, and procurement teams; attend client meetings.</p><p>- Other ad-hoc duties.<br /></p><p>Requirements:</p><p>- Diploma/Degree in QS, Civil Engineering, or related field.</p><p>- Min. 2–3 years’ experience in steelwork QS or contract admin.</p><p>- Strong in cost estimation, negotiation & drawing interpretation.</p><p>- Independent, detail-oriented, and good communication skills.</p><p>- Immediate availability preferred.</p>",
